Someone came to fix the floor in my kitchen, so I'm going to pretend I still have a job and work from home while revising Too Hot to Handle.
If I can manage to open this damned file. (Damn OneDrive.)
*pirate's voice* I'm here.
And that's when it starts to really hit. Great!
Her passive-aggressive way of cranking my air purifier to the max makes me uncomfortable, but it smells like wood shavings, so it's justified even though it's an anti-mask. And besides, I really do need to protect myself, don't I??
I really want to go back to bed, but I can't until he leaves.
The positive thing is that I've finally finished rereading chapter 4!
Chapter five is long, but full of suspense. Good work.
In the process of doing find-and-replace on … ➡️ ellipse character, and there are 54 of them in this chapter 😅
But well, I'm up for it. The most natural speeches are usually choppy, especially when people let themselves go with their emotions.
The handyman is vacuuming, and with a bit of luck, he'll soon be done.
He went out (as far as I can tell) to cut something. So I took a look to see where he is. It's far from being finished :(
Only 7 pages left on chapter five. It's still my favorite chapter, and it's pretty well done. A few layout changes and minor edits to switch to active voice and improve conciseness. That said, I'd really like a break and a cup of tea, but the guy is still tinkering in my kitchen.
He just started vacuuming again. I hope that's a good sign.
The handyman has left!
He told me he had done a quote for the entire floor, but the owners were cheap and only paid for the small damaged area near the door. It's clearly better.
The house is airing out, and my air purifier is running in the kitchen while I enjoy a cup of tea in the garden!
